adaptogen (dstate) session 2026-06-21 (commit cb765ed, pushed claude/serene-maxwell-k11bwl): 'make a workflow, improve every possible aspect'. Two genuine witnessed defects fixed in a very mature codebase (prior passes covered agent-fluency/perf/bugs; further density would be churn). (1) WORKFLOW GAP: only .github/workflows/publish.yml existed, on: push branches:[main] -> pull requests and feature branches had ZERO CI. Added .github/workflows/ci.yml: on pull_request + push branches-ignore:[main], single job 'witness' = setup-bun + bun install + bun test.js + bun run bench, NO publish/version steps so it cannot collide with the main-only publish recursion; concurrency group ci-${{github.ref}} cancel-in-progress. (2) PKG BUG: package.json files[] listed '.claude/skills' but the Agent Skill physically lives at skills/adaptogen/SKILL.md, so npm pack shipped WITHOUT the skill; CHANGELOG feat(skill) entry also had the stale .claude/skills path. Fixed files[] -> 'skills'; npm pack --dry-run now lists skills/adaptogen/SKILL.md (8.1kB); corrected the changelog path. Witnesses: bun test.js 78 assertions OK; bun run bench per_transition_us 396, estimated_replay_cost 1 (flat); python yaml.safe_load parses ci.yml (note: PyYAML coerces the 'on:' key to boolean True, harmless for GitHub Actions); grep non-ASCII over changed files empty. CHANGELOG Unreleased records both. Lesson: 'on:' in GitHub workflow YAML round-trips as boolean True under PyYAML 1.1 -- not a defect.